  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Level\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Anti-Money Laundering (AML) principles\n\n2. United States\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n3. European Union\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Comprehensive regulations for financial institutions\n- Enhanced due diligence requirements\n\n4. Key Regulatory Measures\n- Customer identification procedures\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Cross-border transaction tracking\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
